r.com%2Fmeta-content-moderation-update-impact-ad-business-brand-safety-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epolicy%20on%20hateful%20conduct%3C%2Fa%3E%20earlier%20this%20week%20in%20a%20post%20on%20its%20internal%20forum.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20perspective%20is%20we've%20done%20well%20as%20a%20community%20when%20the%20debate%20has%20happened%20and%20I%20was%20shocked%20with%20how%20far%20we've%20gone%20with%20censorship%20of%20the%20debate%2C%26quot%3B%20Schultz%20wrote%20in%20the%20post%2C%20seen%20by%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20his%20friends%20and%20family%20were%20shocked%20to%20see%20him%20receive%20abuse%20as%20a%20gay%20man%20in%20the%20past%2C%20but%20that%20it%20helped%20them%20to%20realize%20hatred%20exists.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMost%20of%20our%20progress%20on%20rights%20happened%20during%20periods%20without%20mass%20censorship%20like%20this%20and%20pushing%20it%20underground%2C%20I%20think%2C%20has%20coincided%20with%20reversals%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BObviously%2C%20I%20don't%20like%20people%20saying%20things%20that%20I%20consider%20awful%20but%20I%20worry%20that%20the%20solution%20of%20censoring%20that%20doesn't%20work%20as%20well%20as%20you%20might%20hope.%20So%20I%20don't%20know%20the%20answer%2C%20this%20stuff%20is%20really%20complicated%2C%20but%20I%20am%20worried%20that%20too%20much%20censorship%20is%20actually%20harmful%20and%20that's%20may%20have%20been%20where%20we%20ended%20up.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20week%2C%20the%20company%20adjusted%20its%20moderation%20guidelines%20to%20allow%20statements%20on%20its%20platforms%20claiming%20that%20LGBTQ%2B%20people%20are%20%26quot%3Bmentally%20ill%26quot%3B%20and%20removed%20trans%20and%20nonbinary-themed%20chat%20options%20from%20its%20Messenger%20app%2C%20features%20that%20had%20previously%20been%20showcased%20as%20part%20of%20the%20company's%20support%20for%20Pride%20Month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchultz%20also%20said%20that%20he%20does%20not%20think%20that%20censorship%20and%20cancel%20culture%20have%20helped%20the%20LGBTQ%2B%20movement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20wrote%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20enforce%20these%20things%20perfectly%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20cited%20an%20example%20of%20a%20mistake%20of%20taking%20down%20images%20of%20two%20men%20kissing%20and%20removing%20a%20slur%20word%20toward%20gay%20people%20rather%20than%20a%20deliberate%20move%20by%20a%20%26quot%3Bbigoted%20person%20in%20operations.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchultz%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BSo%20the%20more%20rules%20we%20have%2C%20the%20more%20mistakes%20we%20make%E2%80%A6Moderation%20is%20hard%20and%20we'll%20always%20get%20it%20wrong%20somewhat.%20The%20more%20rules%2C%20the%20more%20censorship%2C%20the%20more%20we'll%20harm%20speech%20from%20our%20own%20community%20pushing%20back%20on%20hatred.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company's%20latest%20decision%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-rolls-back-dei-programs-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eroll%20back%20its%20DEI%20programs%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20sparked%20intense%20internal%20debate%20and%20public%20scrutiny.%20The%20announcement%2C%20delivered%20via%20an%20internal%20memo%20by%20VP%20of%20HR%20Janelle%20Gale%2C%20said%20that%20the%20company%20would%20dismantle%20its%20dedicated%20DEI%20team%20and%20eliminate%20diversity%20programs%20in%20its%20hiring%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20said%20Tuesday%20it%20will%20replace%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmetas-fact-checking-exit-prompts-urgent-ifcn-meeting-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethird-party%20fact-checkers%20on%20Facebook%2C%20Instagram%2C%20and%20Threads%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20a%20community%20notes%20system%2C%20mirroring%20the%20approach%20used%20on%20Elon%20Musk's%20platform%2C%20X.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ESchulz%20told%20BI%20in%20an%20interview%20earlier%20this%20week%20that%20the%20election%20of%20Donald%20T