%22_blank%5C%22%3EDonald%20Trump%3C%2Fa%3E's%20second%20term.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20president-elect's%20private%20company%20said%20Trump%20would%20be%20walled%20off%20from%20day-to-day%20duties.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EUnlike%20in%202017%2C%20the%20company%20is%20leaving%20the%20door%20more%20open%20to%20some%20foreign%20transactions.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-organization%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETrump%20Organization%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Friday%20announced%20that%20President-elect%20Donald%20Trump%20will%20be%20walled%20off%20from%20the%20day-to-day%20management%20of%20his%20privately%20held%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20in%202017%2C%20Trump's%20company%20is%20not%20agreeing%20to%20a%20blanket%20stop%20on%20new%20foreign%20business%20transactions.%20Instead%2C%20a%20five-page%20ethics%20plan%20calls%20only%20for%20a%20limit%20on%20transactions%20with%20foreign%20governments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Company%20will%20not%20enter%20into%20any%20new%20material%20transactions%20or%20contracts%20with%20a%20foreign%20government%2C%20except%20for%20Ordinary%20Course%20Transactions%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20a%20copy%20of%20the%20plan%2C%20obtained%20by%20CNBC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20language%20would%20seem%20to%20allow%20business%20dealings%20like%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-golf-deal-liv-pga-tour-rory-mcilroy-musk-2024%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETrump%20Organization's%20work%20with%20LIV%20Golf%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20competitor%20to%20the%20PGA%20financed%20by%20Saudi%20Arabia's%20sovereign%20wealth%20fund%2C%20to%20continue.%20LIV%20is%20set%20to%20return%20to%20Trump%20National%20Doral%20in%20Florida%20for%20an%20April%20tournament.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENoah%20Bookbinder%2C%20president%20of%20Citizens%20for%20Responsibility%20and%20Ethics%20in%20Washington%2C%20said%20the%20company's%20plan%20was%20little%20more%20than%20a%20rehash%20of%20Trump's%20first-term%20ethics%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20saw%20during%20the%20first%20four%20years%20of%20the%20Trump%20presidency%2C%20a%20tremendous%20of%20the%20mixing%20of%20the%20business%20of%20the%20presidency%20with%20all%20kinds%20of%20interests%2C%20companies%2C%20people%20bring%20business%20to%20business%20Donald%20Trump%20seemingly%20as%20a%20way%20to%20kind%20of%20curry%20favor%20with%20him%2C%26quot%3B%20Bookbinder%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20we're%20seeing%20this%20time%20is%20Donald%20Trump%20potentially%20taking%20the%20same%20ethics%20guidelines%20that%20didn't%20work%20during%20his%20first%20presidency%20and%20then%20dialing%20them%20back%20some.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20policies%20outlined%20in%20a%20five-page%20document%20mirror%20Trump's%20promises%20when%20he%20took%20office%20in%202016.%20One%20of%20the%20main%20similarities%20is%20that%20the%20Trump%20Organization%20has%20again%20appointed%20an%20outside%20ethics%20advisor.%20Bill%20Burck%2C%20co-managing%20Partner%20of%20Quinn%20Emanuel%20and%20a%20former%20George%20W.%20Bush%20DOJ%20official%2C%20will%20serve%20as%20the%20advisor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20plan%2C%20Burck%20will%20review%20acquisitions%20over%20%2410%20million%2C%20leases%20involving%20more%20than%2040%2C000%20sq.%20ft.%2C%20and%20new%20debts%20of%20more%20than%20%2410%20million.%20He%20will%20also%20review%20deals%20with%20the%20US%20government%20as%20well%20as%20with%20state%20and%20local%20governments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20first%20reported%20on%20the%20ethics%20plan.%20The%20Journal%20also%20reported%20that%20the%20Trump%20Organization%20wants%20to%20reclaim%20its%20former%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20hotel.%20Congressional%20Democrats%20sued%20Trump%20when%20he%20was%20in%20office%2C%20alleging%20he%20was%20partly%20violating%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-said-emoluments-clause-in-us-constitution-is-phony-2019-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20Constitution's%20emoluments%20clause%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0by%20renting%20out%20hotel%20rooms%20to%20foreign%20governments.%20In%202021%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20threw%20out%20the%20remaining%20emoluments-related%20lawsuits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20has%20significant%20assets%20outside%20of%20his%20eponymous%20firm.%20He%20has%20a%20significant%20stake%20in%20Trump%20Media%20%26amp%3B%20Technology%20Group%2C%20the%20parent%20company%20of%20his%20social%20media%20platform%20Truth%20Social.%20Trump's%20shares%20are%20a%20large%20part%20of%20the%20reason%20why%20his%20net%20worth%20is%20now%20estimated%20to%20be%20over%20%246%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-ethics-trump-organization-foreign-business-white-house-2025-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1736543495000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67817bf188b000981b4a7488%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-ethics-trump-organization-foreign-business-white-house-2025-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Unlike%20in%202017%2C%20Trump's%20company%20is%20not%20agreeing%20to%20a%20blanket%20stop%20on%20new%20foreign%20business%20transactions.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22bgriffiths%40insider.com%20(Brent%20D.%20Griffiths)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A12%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-ethics-trump-organization-foreign-business-white-house-2025-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22L.A.%20Reporters%20Cover%20Devastation%20in%20Their%20Own%20Neighborhoods%20During%20Wildfires%3A%20%E2%80%98Feels%20Like%20a%20Nightmare%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98Fatigue%20Is%20Setting%20In%E2%80%99%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1736543214000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fu