%20pass%20allowing%20them%20to%20get%20away%20with%20murder.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWar%20Crimes%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Afghanistan%20Inquiry%2C%20commissioned%20by%20the%20UK%20government's%20Ministry%20of%20Defence%20(MoD)%20in%202022%2C%20is%20investigating%20alleged%20war%20crimes%20by%20British%20armed%20forces%20during%20the%20Afghan%20conflict.%20The%20focus%20lies%20particularly%20on%20the%20actions%20of%20UK%20Special%20Forces%20(UKSF)%20units%20during%20night-time%20raids%20known%20as%20'deliberate%20detention%20operations'.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20testimonies%20from%20seven%20UKSF%20personnel%20-%20given%20in%20secret%20due%20to%20national%20security%20concerns%20-%20troops%20carried%20out%20killings%20of%20unarmed%20Afghans%2C%20including%20individuals%20who%20posed%20no%20threat.%20One%20soldier%2C%20referred%20to%20as%20N1799%20in%20the%20documents%2C%20testified%20that%20during%20some%20operations%2C%20%26quot%3Ball%20fighting-age%20males%20were%20killed%20on%20target%20regardless%20of%20the%20threat%20they%20posed.%26quot%3B%20He%20recounted%20hearing%20that%20detainees%20were%20executed%20in%20compounds%2C%20sometimes%20using%20methods%20such%20as%20placing%20a%20pillow%20over%20a%20victim's%20head%20before%20shooting%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20inquiry%20heard%20that%20some%20victims%20of%20these%20killings%20were%20under%20the%20age%20of%2016.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EEvidence%20Of%20Cover-Up%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEmails%20and%20witness%20accounts%20provided%20to%20the%20inquiry%20show%20concerns%20among%20certain%20officers%20about%20the%20conduct%20of%20UKSF%20units.%20In%20one%20email%20from%20February%202011%2C%20an%20officer%20questioned%20whether%20SAS%20soldiers%20were%20deliberately%20setting%20up%20scenarios%20to%20justify%20killings%2C%20such%20as%20ordering%20detainees%20to%20retrieve%20weapons%20before%20shooting%20them.%20A%20senior%20officer%20acknowledged%20the%20issue%2C%20stating%20that%20there%20appeared%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Ba%20casual%20disregard%20for%20life%26quot%3B%20and%20counterinsurgency%20principles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20officer%2C%20known%20as%20N2107%2C%20referred%20to%20the%20SAS%20and%20%26quot%3Bmurder%26quot%3B%20as%20%26quot%3Bregular%20bedfellows%26quot%3B%20in%20emails.%20He%20told%20the%20inquiry%20that%20by%202011%2C%20he%20believed%20SAS%20units%20were%20committing%20extrajudicial%20killings.%20However%2C%20he%20admitted%20failing%20to%20escalate%20his%20concerns%20up%20the%20chain%20of%20command%2C%20which%20he%20now%20views%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bmassive%20failure%20of%20leadership.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETestimonies%20show%20that%20operations%20were%20manipulated%20to%20suggest%20weapons%20were%20found%20alongside%20those%20killed%2C%20even%20when%20the%20individuals%20were%20unarmed.%20One%20soldier%20recounted%20being%20told%20that%20photos%20were%20staged%20to%20give%20the%20appearance%20that%20those%20killed%20had%20been%20combatants.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20officer%20described%20the%20SAS%20as%20being%20%26quot%3Bbeyond%20reproach%26quot%3B%20and%20said%20that%20questioning%20their%20actions%20was%20discouraged.%20An%20email%20revealed%20that%20support%20staff%20in%20Afghanistan%20who%20doubted%20the%20credibility%20of%20SAS%20reports%20were%20reprimanded%20to%20ensure%20they%20supported%20the%20%26quot%3Bguys%20on%20the%20ground.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20senior%20officer%20told%20the%20inquiry%20that%20in%20the%20eyes%20of%20UKSF%20leadership%2C%20the%20SAS%20%26quot%3Bcould%20do%20no%20wrong.%26quot%3B%20This%20attitude%20allowed%20the%20regiment%20to%20operate%20with%20near-total%20impunity%2C%20with%20a%20focus%20on%20%26quot%3Bkill%20counts%26quot%3B%20rather%20than%20lawful%20conduct.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPolitical%20Implications%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20allegations%20against%20UKSF%20have%20drawn%20comparisons%20to%20accusations%20of%20misconduct%20by%20US%20special%20operations%20forces%20during%20the%20Afghan%20conflict.%20British%20military%20police%20previously%20conducted%20investigations%20into%20allegations%20of%20war%20crimes%20by%20the%20SAS%20but%20concluded%20that%20there%20was%20insufficient%20evidence%20for%20prosecutions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20MoD%20has%20refrained%20from%20commenting%20further%2C%20stating%20that%20it%20is%20%26quot%3Bappropriate%20to%20await%20the%20outcome%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20inquiry.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20witnesses%20expressed%20fears%20about%20speaking%20out%2C%20citing%20concerns%20for%20their%20safety.%20N1799%2C%20for%20example%2C%20requested%20that%20two%20MoD%20representatives%20be%20removed%20from%20the%20inquiry%20room%20before%20he%20gave%20evidence%2C%20stating%20that%20he%20felt%20%26quot%3Ba%20bit%20sick.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1736507460000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-01%2Fbqum1hro_british-sas-generic-_625x300_10_January_25.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fuk-special-forces-had-golden-pass-to-get-away-with-murder-in-afghanistan-7443057%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22An%20inquiry%20into%20the%20actions%20of%20British%20special%20forces%20in%20Afghanistan%20has%20uncovered%20allegations%20of%20extrajudicial%20killings%20and%20efforts%20to%20cover%20up%20unlawful%20actions%20during%20the%20war.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fuk-special-forces-had-golden-pass-to-get-away-with-murder-in-afghanistan-7443057%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ex%20Rapido%20Driver%20Arrested%20From%20Delhi%20For%20Supplying%20Illegal%20Liquor%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%20man%2C%20formerly%20employed%20with%20Rapido%2C%20the%20largest%20player%20in%20bike%20taxis%2C%20was%20arrested%20while%20supplying%20illegal%20liq